<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-06T08:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-06T08:29:00-05:00" n="172" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/570</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-06T17:00:00+03:31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 6, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 7, 3.55
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1842. Awaiting reply to my 1808, September 27, 11 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d172fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_196">p.
                                    196</ref>.</note> New Ministry will be announced to-day or
                                to-morrow to which opposition unlikely, after which Allied
                                Ambassadors will present to the Government joint note of the
                                character outlined. They will act jointly October 9, without me
                                unless I am authorized to unite therein.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>